headline: 'This Is Just A Necessary Spend': Back-To-School Spending Holds Steady Despite Economic Uncertainties
summary: Summer may be just getting underway, but plenty of parents are already planning their spending for the upcoming school year. headline: Lululemon's lawsuit against Costco highlights the rise of fashion 'dupes'
summary: Fashion “dupes,” or less expensive versions of high-end clothing and other accessories, are just about everywhere these days.  In the latest example, Lululemon slapped a lawsuit against Costco on Friday, accusing the wholesale club operator of selling lower-priced duplicates of some of its popular athleisure apparel. headline: Will Tariff-Induced Supply Chain Unpredictability Grinch-ify 'Christmas in July'?
summary: In last year's 48-hour window, Amazon Prime Day set a record of $14.2 billion in sales revenue. The online retail giant has increased the duration of its biggest sales event of the year to four days in 2025, running from July 8 to July 11. Walmart, Target, Best Buy, Kohl's and other retailers are attempting to get the jump on Amazon by starting their versions of "Black Friday in July" sales events on July 7, with some running past July 11.
